---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="CMS" description="Use Pages CMS to edit posts and upload images from a web UI.">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">CMS</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">Visual Editing</h1>
      <p class="page-lead">
        This site is connected to Pages CMS, a Git-backed editor for Markdown and media files.
        Sign in with GitHub, open this repository, and edit content in a browser.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="entry-grid">
      <article class="entry-card">
        <h2 class="entry-card__title">Open the editor</h2>
        <p class="entry-card__description">
          Sign in at Pages CMS and choose the repository <code>CxyEstella/CxyEstella.github.io</code>.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__actions">
          <a
            class="button-link button-link--primary"
            href="https://app.pagescms.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            Open Pages CMS
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="entry-card">
        <h2 class="entry-card__title">What it edits well</h2>
        <p class="entry-card__description">
          Regular posts, notes, tags, descriptions, dates, body text, and uploaded images work well in
          the visual editor.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry-card">
        <h2 class="entry-card__title">Where uploads go</h2>
        <p class="entry-card__description">
          Images uploaded from the CMS are saved in <code>public/uploads/</code> and can be reused
          across all collections.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry-card">
        <h2 class="entry-card__title">Good to know</h2>
        <p class="entry-card__description">
          Advanced MDX patterns and some math-heavy posts are still safer to review in a code editor
          before publishing.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
